With lockdowns in place around the world, we know that the experience of staying indoors is very different depending on your access to outdoor space. We’d like to hear how your access to space has impacted you over the last three weeks. Perhaps you’re in a flat without a garden, or don’t have parks or outdoor areas nearby. Alternatively, perhaps your access to a local green space has helped you to cope with coronavirus measures. You can get in touch by filling in the form below. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact for publication before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.